(1. Executive Summary) Tj
0 -14 Td
0 -14 Td
(Locomotion is a full-stack ride booking and real-time mobility platform with rider, driver,) Tj
0 -14 Td
(and admin workflows. The system combines a React web frontend, a Django + DRF backend with) Tj
0 -14 Td
(real-time Channels, a FastAPI AI service, and an Expo React Native mobile app. The production) Tj
0 -14 Td
(backend runs on a single-node k3s cluster on AWS EC2 using Helm, with Docker images built in) Tj
0 -14 Td
(GitHub Actions and stored in AWS ECR.) Tj
0 -14 Td
0 -14 Td
(2. Architecture Overview) Tj
0 -14 Td
0 -14 Td
(Core runtime components:) Tj
0 -14 Td
(Web frontend: React 19 with Vite) Tj
0 -14 Td
(Backend API: Django + Django REST Framework) Tj
0 -14 Td
(Real-time: Django Channels + Redis) Tj
0 -14 Td
(Background jobs: Celery + Celery Beat) Tj
0 -14 Td
(AI service: FastAPI + Qdrant + SentenceTransformers + Gemini/Groq) Tj
0 -14 Td
(Mobile: Expo React Native \(driver app\)) Tj
0 -14 Td
0 -14 Td
(Core infrastructure services:) Tj
0 -14 Td
(PostgreSQL: transactional data) Tj
0 -14 Td
(Redis: cache, channel layer, Celery broker) Tj
0 -14 Td
(DynamoDB: ride location history) Tj
0 -14 Td
(S3: media storage) Tj
0 -14 Td
(SQS: notification queue) Tj
0 -14 Td
(Firebase Cloud Messaging: push delivery) Tj
0 -14 Td
(ECR: backend image registry) Tj
0 -14 Td
(EC2 + k3s: runtime cluster) Tj
0 -14 Td
0 -14 Td
(3. Data and Storage) Tj
0 -14 Td
0 -14 Td
(PostgreSQL stores users, drivers, vehicles, bookings, payments, and notifications.) Tj
0 -14 Td
(Redis supports real-time Channels and Celery background processing.) Tj
0 -14 Td
(DynamoDB stores sampled ride location history for admin playback and analytics.) Tj
0 -14 Td
(S3 stores user-uploaded media.) Tj
0 -14 Td
(SQS decouples notification delivery from request flow.) Tj
0 -14 Td
0 -14 Td
(4. Notification Flow) Tj
0 -14 Td
0 -14 Td
(Current production notification path:) Tj
0 -14 Td
(1. Django publishes notification payloads to SQS.) Tj
0 -14 Td
(2. AWS Lambda consumes SQS and sends FCM pushes.) Tj
0 -14 Td
0 -14 Td
(The legacy Kubernetes notification worker remains available for local or fallback use, but the) Tj
0 -14 Td
(production Helm values disable it.) Tj
0 -14 Td
0 -14 Td
